Sentencas: In this study one step co-synthesis method is investigated to prepare La0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta (LSCFN-GDC), with the purpose of developing a facile and optimized electrode fabrication procedure for Zirconia electrolyte based symmetric solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Co-synthesis of LSCFN-GDC electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell running on propane

Sentencas: The co-synthesized LSCFN-GDC shows distinct co-existence of perovskite and fluorite structure with high chemical compatibility and remarkable optimized electrode microstructure compared with the physical mixing one.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of LSCFN-GDC electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell running on propane

Sentencas: The particle size of both LSCFN and GDC are obviously decreased and the electrode porosity is increased using the co-synthesized method.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of LSCFN-GDC electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell running on propane

Sentencas: As a result, the polarization resistance of LSCFN-GDC electrode is dramatically decreased to 0.022 Omega.cm(2), compared with 0.051 U cm(2) of the physical mixing one, at 850 similar to C in air.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of LSCFN-GDC electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell running on propane

Sentencas: Symmetrical single cells with a configuration of LSCFN-GDC parallel to GDC vertical bar YSZ vertical bar GDC parallel to LSCFN-GDC are successfully fabricated and characterized under various fuels of H-2, CH4 and C3H8.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of LSCFN-GDC electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell running on propane

Sentencas: Results show that, the maximum power densities are discovered to be 348mW.cm(-2) and 324mW.cm(-2) at 850 degrees C under room temperature humidified hydrogen and propane, respectively, yielding a tremendous cell performance improvement.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of LSCFN-GDC electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell running on propane

Sentencas: Moreover, the long-term operation of such symmetrical single cell is demonstrated to be stable for more than 100 h under both hydrogen and propane.
Titulo: Co-synthesis of LSCFN-GDC electrode for symmetric solid oxide fuel cell running on propane
